name: nonexistent paintings #001 - a painting of a burning police car
description:
text prompt: a painting of a burning police car
(single frame, 40 iterations per frame using VQGAN+CLIP)

this painting is the result of the thinking process of the following questions, "art according to what? / unified society according to who?" with the help of artificial intelligence.

generative art refers to any art practice where the artist uses a system,
such as a set of natural language rules, a computer program, a machine, or other
procedural invention, which is set into motion with some degree of autonomy
contributing to or resulting in a completed work of art.
